+++ ###0a0|This component has been adjusted for Sigma-9[[footnote]]The former default site theme. Some language branches, sister sites, and sandboxes may still use it.[[/footnote]] and -10[[footnote]]The current site theme on the English wiki, an updated version of Sigma-9.[[/footnote]] based themes.##
Black Highlighter themes are not supported yet.
+++ ðŸŒˆTo use this component, insert this line into the source code of your page:
For Sigma-10:
> [[include :scp-wiki:component:pride-logos s10=-]| ###0a0|code=##**input the code on the second row below in the showcase table**]]
Example:
> [[include :scp-wiki:component:pride-logos s10=-]| ###0a0|code=##trans]]
For Sigma-9:
> [[include :scp-wiki:component:pride-logos s9=-]| ###0a0|code=##**input the code**]]
Example:
> [[include :scp-wiki:component:pride-logos s9=-]| ###0a0|code=##trans]]

[[collapsible show="+ Show Customization options" hide="- Hide Customization options" hideLocation="both"]]

+++ ðŸŒˆCombine Two

You can fuse/join two logos together, one half on the left side, another half on the right side by introducing a **{{code2}}** attribute:
> [[include :scp-wiki:component:pride-logos s10=-]| ###0a0|code=##**code for the left half** |##blue|code2=##**code for the right half**]]
Example:
> [[include :scp-wiki:component:pride-logos s10=-]| ###0a0|code=##nonbinary |##blue|code2=##pan]]
This will put together the nonbinary flag and pan pride flag to make a whole logo, and might be useful for those who hope to display two identities.
~~~~
[[include :scp-wiki:component:image-block
|name=https://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/local--files/component:pride-logos/scp-join.png
|caption=Preview
|width=100px
|align=center
]]
~~~~
If you think it looks better to join the two halves by a different angle, just add the **{{angle}}** attribute to change the division to non-vertical:
> [[include :scp-wiki:component:pride-logos s10=-]| ###0a0|code=##**code for the first logo** |##blue|code2=##**code for the second logo** |##crimson|angle=##**The tilt angle of the seam, 0-360**]]
At 0Â° it will be combined horizontally. The default setting is vertical (90Â°). The tilt angle starts from the left (negative x-axis) then clockwise.

E.g. this will change the dividing angle to 60Â°ï¼š
> [[include :scp-wiki:component:pride-logos s10=-]| ###0a0|code=##nonbinary |##blue|code2=##pan |##crimson|angle=##60]]
~~~~
[[include :scp-wiki:component:image-block
|name=https://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/local--files/component:pride-logos/scp-join2.png
|caption=Preview
|width=100px
|align=center
]]
~~~~
+++ ðŸŒˆUpload Your Own Image

If the ready-made logos listed below didn't satisfy you, this will assure you a chance to make your own pride! Just use the **{{custom}}** attribute to insert a URL:
> [[include :scp-wiki:component:pride-logos s10=-]| ##darkorchid|custom=##url(**URL of your custom image**)]]
The combination technique (including the angle option) still works, and you can upload another image:
> [[include :scp-wiki:component:pride-logos s10=-]| ##darkorchid|custom=##url(**URL of your custom image**)| ##dodgerblue|custom2=##url(**another URL of your custom image**)]]
Images with a equal width and height will work best, otherwise it will be scaled and stretched. 

+++ ðŸŒˆMore Advanced Effects for CSS Veterans

//Q: Can I assemble 3 or more logos, or opt for other advanced effects (gradients, animation[[footnote]]Currently, @keyframe animation cannot directly apply to the mask-image property.[[/footnote]], etc.)?//

Theoretically, of course. As you can see, this page has a sample logo in which the rainbow flag softly fades into white. This component uses a CSS mask to cut the secondary logo to a half, then put it precisely on the top of the first logo. It is designed to cut at 50% sharp:

[[code type="css"]]
mask-image: linear-gradient(to right, transparent 50%, black 50%);
[[/code]]

CSS masks can blend two images by displaying one of them only within the scope of the mask. So linear gradients, radial gradients, and even CSS animations are all feasible.

Simply add the **{{mask}}** attribute to override the existing mask-image:

> [[include :scp-wiki:component:pride-logos s10=-]| ##fuchsia|mask=##**gradients, svgs, or something else**]]

For reference, the gradient logo for this page is coded as:
[[code type="css"]]
mask-image: linear-gradient(60deg, transparent 30%, black 60%);
[[/code]]
In this case, only the **{{linear-gradient(60deg, transparent 30%, black 60%)}}** field is required. The former **{{angle}}** attribute will then be rendered invalid. It shall be written as:

> [[include :scp-wiki:component:pride-logos s10=-]| ###0a0|code=##default| ##blue|code2=##pride| ##fuchsia|mask=##linear-gradient(60deg, transparent 30%, black 60%)]]

However, to put 3 or more images together isn't this simple. You might need to use another pseudo-element (#header::after), and set the linear-gradient to 33%, 66% or something. Due to the complexity, these functions are not implemented here.

//Q: Can I insert my own pride flag into the transparent logo frame?//

Yes, but a bit complicated. A possible method: set the flag as the secondary background-image or header::after, then clip it with another logo-shaped mask-image.
[[/collapsible]]
